OVERVIEW:
SectorWars 2102 resource economy covering 7 core trading commodities, strategic resources (quantum shards, population), and rare materials with price ranges, acquisition methods, and strategic uses.

FACTS:
* 7 core trading commodities: Ore, Basic Food, Gourmet Food, Fuel, Technology, Exotic Technology, Luxury Goods
* 4 strategic resources: Population, Quantum Shards, Quantum Crystals, Genesis Devices
* 2 rare materials: Prismatic Ore, Photonic Crystals
* Port classes (0-11) determine commodity buy/sell availability
* Prices fluctuate based on supply/demand and regional variations
* 5 Quantum Shards combine to create 1 Quantum Crystal
* Quantum Crystals required for player-created warp gates
* Population available from region's Sector 1 population hub at 50 credits/unit
* Each population unit occupies 1 cargo space during transport
* Credits never stored on ship (virtual, never lost on destruction)
* Team treasury supports 12 resource types for shared storage

TERMINOLOGY:
* Commodity: Tradeable resource bought/sold at ports
* Strategic Resource: Special materials for advanced gameplay
* Rare Material: Extremely uncommon resources with unique properties
* Port Class: Determines which commodities port buys/sells
* Market Dynamics: Supply/demand price fluctuations
* Team Treasury: Shared resource storage for team members

CORE_COMMODITIES:
Ore:
  price_range: 15-45 credits/unit
  usage: Construction, manufacturing, repairs
  value_pattern: Highest in industrial sectors, lowest near mining operations
  description: Universal currency of construction

BasicFood:
  price_range: 8-25 credits/unit
  usage: Population survival, colonization requirement
  value_pattern: Highest in overcrowded sectors, lowest near agricultural worlds
  description: Minimum requirement for colonization

GourmetFood:
  price_range: 30-70 credits/unit
  usage: Enhanced colony development, production efficiency boost
  value_pattern: Highest in wealthy sectors, rarely found in frontier
  description: Luxury foodstuffs and exotic ingredients

Fuel:
  price_range: 20-60 credits/unit
  usage: Ship propulsion, station operations
  value_pattern: Highest in remote sectors, lowest near refining operations
  consumption: Increases with ship size and travel distance

Technology:
  price_range: 50-120 credits/unit
  usage: Ship upgrades, advanced infrastructure
  value_pattern: Highest in frontier sectors, lowest near industrial hubs
  description: Advanced components and equipment

ExoticTechnology:
  price_range: 150-300 credits/unit
  usage: Cutting-edge modifications, specialized facilities
  value_pattern: Highest in research sectors/military outposts
  description: Rare prototypes and experimental devices

LuxuryGoods:
  price_range: 75-200 credits/unit
  usage: High-end merchandise demand satisfaction
  value_pattern: Highest in wealthy central sectors, lowest in production zones
  profit: Highest margins but volatile markets

STRATEGIC_RESOURCES:
Population:
  cost: 50 credits/unit
  source: Region's Sector 1 population hub
  cargo_space: 1 unit per population
  colonization_requirement: 10,000 units minimum
  growth: Natural expansion after planet establishment
  usage: Required for planet colonization and population growth

QuantumShards:
  rarity: Very rare
  acquisition: Found in nebulae and anomalies
  usage: 5 shards â†’ 1 Quantum Crystal
  locations: Dangerous unexplored regions
  description: Crystalline fragments with exotic energy

QuantumCrystals:
  rarity: Extremely rare
  creation: Assemble 5 Quantum Shards at specialized facilities
  usage: Essential for player-created warp gates
  strategic_value: Enables custom navigation networks

GenesisDevices:
  usage: Create new colonizable planet in empty sector
  ship_capacity: 0-5 depending on ship type
  strategic_use: Custom territory expansion

RARE_MATERIALS:
PrismaticOre:
  rarity: Extremely rare (1 in 10,000 asteroids)
  usage: Ultra-lightweight hull reinforcement, superior ship construction
  acquisition: Extensive asteroid field exploration and mining

PhotonicCrystals:
  rarity: Very rare (specific nebula types only)
  usage: Advanced sensors, energy weapon enhancement
  acquisition: Navigate through dangerous nebula clouds

